byteStream() API returns "InputStream", in my previous comment when I said "sync" read I mean that the InputStream::read API itself is blocking. i.e. can't do something like below with IS:
InputStream.readAsync(bytes_count, new CallBack(byte[] bytes) {
});
So even though we can asynchronously return BlobDownloadResponse, we can't asynchronously read the content:
downloadAsync(params, new CallBack<BlobDownloadResponse>() {
    // This is async
    public void onResponse(BlobDownloadResponse res) {
         // below read is not async but sync.
         res.resposeBody.byteStream().read();
    }
}
